ry group friendly and I'm extremely willing to play with just about any group mate that's LFG when I have a slot open in my group... including Wizards.  Moreover, I know several Wizards and we've spoken on many occasions as to their relative strengths and weaknesses.<br>
<br>
Recently a specific zone (Cazic Thule) revealed to me the TRUE strength of the Wizard.  Cazic has AE'ing Justicar mobs that are really much too nasty for melee-centric groups to handle efficiently.  Add a wizard to your group mix, however, and these mobs become absolute CAKE.<br>
<br>
My solution (or recommendation) for VI, is for all zones to have a mixture of mobs that contain at least a significant percentage of these types of mobs -- specifically, Low hit points, high DPS, and high annoyance factor for melee-type groups.<br>
<br>
These &quot;nasty mobs&quot; or &quot;Designed-for-DD mobs&quot; must have low HPs, at least few enough to be viable to burn em down, maybe ranging from one-third to two-thirds of a melee mob of the same level.  To prevent wizards from simply soloing them (and thereby continuing to avoid groups), they must all summon when hurt.  Finally, they need to be mixed into the zones in such a way that it's not really viable to just skip them...  if each spawn point has a random chance of spawning one of these mobs then a melee group &quot;pick and choosing&quot; melee-centric mobs will eventually run out of melee groups -- whereas if there's a group containing a Wizard (or other nukers) they will happily pulling these extra &quot;nasty mobs&quot; for their own benefit, since they die so fast and so efficiently that they'd end up being Great EXP.<br>
<br>
I think that &gt;&gt;THIS&lt;&lt; is the real solution to improving Wizards' desirability in groups.  Not by adding new spells, nor necessarily removing any -- although that by improving Wizards (and actually druids and necros by proxy) grouping viability in this manner it might be required to de-tune the ease of Soloing as a Wizard, maybe only in the High end (60+).<br>
<br>
As has been posted on several other threads relating to nerfing Snare as a counter balance some improvement in your Grouping desirability I propose a zone-by-zone modification of Snare.  Where zones have been improved with these new DD-optimized mob types perhaps Snare could be modified as well, to make snare's effects diminish the further a hated-Player is from a mob.  At 50 feet, snare could have NO effect.  At 10 feet, full effect.  This would eliminate snare for SOLOING, but maintain its strength to park Runners... and this code exists today in the Druid spell Sunbeam. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=aliannasedai>Alianna Sedai</A> at: 11/11/02 3:04:08 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=pidmaster>pidmaster</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/12/02 1:07 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A Solution to Wizard Desirability (Recommendation to VI)</span><hr size=1> YES!!<br>
<br>
