<br>
The problem is that people will just choose to avoid theses places or whine about them until they are nefted.<br>
<br>
I believe that verant sees wizards as the masters of lure base damage. We also get flexiable damage in the form of fire, magic and cold based nukes. (note I believe verant gives a noticiable bias towards wizard cold nukes)<br>
<br>
The perfect wizard only mobs<br>
Hit hard, High DS (non MT melee take damage) ,Very high AC ( hard to melee), high resists (esp Fire and magic), and low hp.<br>
Note high resists = hard to land snare = hard to quad.<br>
These mobs have to have hps such that the amount of mana needed to kill a normal mob using normal nukes is the same as that used to kill these via lure nukes.<br>
<br>
The High DS is very important. Its what biases the group towards a caster vs another melee class.<br>
Healer Mana is the bottleneck in amost every encounter.<br>
In a one healer (cleric say) rest melee group only the MT requires the consumption of mana.<br>
The additional melee damage is at no additional mana cost.<br>
On mobs with a DS this is not true.<br>
With a DS mob additional melee take damage and hence mana to heal.<br>
<br>
The strenght of the DS has to be such that the amount of mana used to heal the non MT melee matches that used by a caster to do the same damage as that melee during the course of the fight.<br>
(This is of course screwed up some what by the stupid CH spell)<br>
eg a 10khp mob. Three melee with exactly the same hit points doing exactly the same damage. Each one does 3.3 khp damage. If it takes a caster two casts of a 400 mana nuke to equal that damage then each of the non MT melee should need two CH's (2 x 400 mana) to heal them from the DS during the fight.<br>
Yes I know that because of CH the tanks could have 7500hp each and hence the DS is doing twice that, 15000hp, on each.<br>
<br>
The issue of wizards soloing over grouping is really and issue of being able to quad.<br>
At higher levels this gets much harder anyway (traps in ME, Mobs that hit much harder and take several re-snares and so on)<br>
I don't agree with summoning mobs/ unsnareable/ un rootable mobs as a solution to quading. Why.. because it extremly limits the ability to avoid or escape from a fight.<br>
There is nothing more anoying than getting killed trying to get from A to B with no chance of escape.<br>
<br>
A wizard should be allow to single kite mobs.<br>
I live in Australia. Sometimes there are simply not enought people on to get a group.<br>
Spending 2 hours (8pm to 10pm my time) to get into a group with very bad combination of classes that breaks up after 10 mins really sucks. Its normally 11pm before I get into a half decent group. That means playing to 1 to 2 am in the morning.<br>
This isn't a class problem its a numbers problem.<br>
<br>
I must be able to kill something for 2 or 3hr before the US people start appearing.<br>
<br>
Moozoo Sorcerer<br>
